### AI Service API Testing
### Use the REST Client extension in VS Code to run these requests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Root Endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Chat - Non-streaming (Simple message)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Hello! What can you help me with?",
  "stream": false
}

### Chat - Non-streaming (With conversation history)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What did I just ask you?",
  "history": {
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "system",
        "content": "You are a helpful AI assistant."
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "What is the capital of France?"
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "The capital of France is Paris."
      }
    ]
  },
  "stream": false
}

### Chat - Streaming
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Tell me a short joke",
  "stream": true
}

### Chat - Streaming with history
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Can you tell me another one?",
  "history": {
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "Tell me a joke"
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "Why did the programmer quit his job? Because he didn't get arrays!"
      }
    ]
  },
  "stream": true
}

### Chat - Complex conversation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What's 2+2?",
  "history": {
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "system",
        "content": "You are a math tutor that explains concepts clearly."
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "I need help with basic math"
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "I'd be happy to help you with basic math! What would you like to learn?"
      }
    ]
  },
  "stream": false
}
